Elizabeth Dawes, 39, was told she had invasive grade three breast cancer .
Doctors at New Cross Hospital in Wolverhampton told her she needed immediate surgery and chemotherapy .
But four days later she was asked to attend an appointment with her consultant .
Four days later, she was told staff had confused her notes with those of other patients .
Ms Dawes was so traumatised she needed anti-depressants and was forced to give up her job in the oncology department at the hospital .